						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: Kulōttuṅga III Year 30: 1208 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription records a gift of two <hi rend="italic">paḻaṅkāśu</hi> by a resident of Malaiyampākkam for burning a twilight lamp to the god of Tirunīrmalai. The priest of the temple, Aruḷāḷa Bhaṭṭan received the gift and agreed to burn the lamp perpetually. </p>						

						</summary>
